Method Detail

processCharacteristicValue

protected ChTemperatureMeasurement.TemperatureMeasurementValue processCharacteristicValue()
Description copied from class: BleCharacteristic
Converts the raw characteristic value into the human friendly ValueType.

For example, a heart rate measurement may contain both the heart rate value and several RR-intervals. BluetoothGattCharacteristic returns the value as a byte array. The purpose of this method is to parse the byte array and create a strongly typed data structure.

The implementation is expected to call BleCharacteristic.getBaseGattCharacteristic() to access the underlying characteristic and use one of its get*Value methods to get the raw characteristic value.
